Oh me dad did that, that was his - work. He used to bring eggs - you know, it used to be egg - eggs in the house - for us and he had a nice lot. 'Cos he'd go a nice big garden you know at the back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
No, not every day, I think we used to have - we used to have a lot of lettuce, me dad growed lettuce and was very fond of that. Lettuce and - and spring onions you know we used to - used to have. Perhaps we should have them at tea time. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Can you remember about how often you would have had meat?
