\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7368700\charrsid12715645 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
phone records. But that was - not like they are today. They were rounded. Round and the horn on. A round pun and the horn on. And - that. I can remember that, but - we had that. Oh used to play that. A lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you say your sister learnt the violin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes. Piano as well. Oh she got her own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 So you had a piano in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes. Oh aye, we all used to get round and sing and do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Who played the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Me sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. No. I never learned.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. Me sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Was there anyone in the family who sang, you say they did, was anyone specially good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Well - well we was all good singers in them days. Yes, I was meself 'til I - begun to wonder why I couldn't sing you know a few years ago, found out that the trouble was this lump. I couldn't do anything. Could never find out and
 then - then now I've realized what it was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 So you had sing-songs in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Oh yes. Quite a lot, we used to do a lot of - singing you know in the front room. Mother used to put a fire in and - sister used to play and we used to sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Where did your sister get this music gift from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
I don't know. And she were very good at making - making - lovely dolls clothes. And her own clothes, well me youngest sister now - she does a lot of machining and and - for herself and her clothes. But - I was more on the cooking side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Dominoes. But never cards. Now I never did learn that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did they disapprove of cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes, they did a lot. I've heard them - yes, I've heard 'em say it's gam - it's gambling was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes. Sunday school prizes and - other books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes, we used to have the newspapers. And Post at night, happenny Post. Yes, was, yes. Post boy used to bring 'em, 
and we used to have - what they call a - Police Budget, it were a pink paper in them days. All sorts of murders and things in that had happened. And - and the - Police budget. And - what was the other two? We used to have three. Was it the Express? Someth
ing I know. News of the World. Think News of the World was one, that's been going for many years that has. Yes, we used to have that. And there was - another me dad used to like. I can't think what that one was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Magazines did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes, we used to have - church magazines come. And then - people's give us magazines. And we sat and, you know, to read them and that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes, me dad - read you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did they ever read aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, he used to be very quiet at - you know, used to sit and read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you remember a funeral in the family a long time ago?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Only me sister's. Only me - grandma, me mother's mother. Remember her, she died at sixty-one. Well - of c
ourse I weren't - ever so old then. But I - I knowed - only I - I was old enough to know, 'cos I - I'd been to me grandma - mother used to send me with things to - to me grandma's. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you know who would have gone to the funeral in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Me mother went and me dad. But not - not us, we didn't go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did they wear mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh - mourning. They did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Can you tell me about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Were all black you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 The children as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. Not unless you was older and then they wore a black band round. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 But your parents would have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Yes. That - that - I think that's about the only one I can remember in my young days. But - oh I can - oh I - remember - two of me mother's dying. But we never went to the funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 How long did your mother have to wear mourning, do you remember that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well they - they used to wear it for a nice few months. Then, but - now - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 I have - I've taken the children out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Were you taken when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, I think me mother - looked after us, you know, never - I can't remember anyone taking us out. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Were you taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes, with me mother. Oh yes, we used - yes. Well we used to have to go up Arnold with her as well, to carry the - basket and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you ever go out just with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes, I went out with him occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you remember any outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Only to aunts and uncles. That's all. You didn't go far in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 You went with one parent more than the other did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Of course I went with me mother a lot you know, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Can you ever remember going out on a Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes. Walking to Trent Bridge and walking back. And that - and - and to the Arboretum. Walked there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 All the way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
All the way, and it were - now - oh dear - makes me think. Right down past Midland Station, right down to Trent Bridge, and ben there - hours, in - you know, playing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 It must be every bit of five miles there and five miles back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh what? It was. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you enjoy it or did you think it was rather hard work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well we used to get tired at finish you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you do anything special when you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Paddle you know, paddle in the water, not where it was dangerous you know, 'cos you was warned. And that, we used to - take our sandwiches and - sometimes we had a bottle of pop, sometimes a bottle of water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
I once went to - Shirebrook to me - mother's sisters for a holiday. Once went there and - a friend went with me. Can remember going on that then. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Was it just you and a friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Mm. A girl - schoolgirl you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Were you away long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Well - during holidays. And - that were in - well, before I left school. And then - after I left school - the only holiday I had - was with - two girl friends. We went to Blackpool. That was first time I went to the seaside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 How old were you then, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh - getting on for - what would it be, eighteen. Or nineteen, somewhere about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 How long were you away for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 A week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 That was a real adventure wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Three pound. 
I went with. Paid the board there. And - had a nice holiday you know, dancing and - and doing. And - on the beach and that, sitting down in the deck chairs and that. Pass - you know, passing time on. Then back again for - your tea. Then there was your - y
our money you know as you got over when you paid - paid for your board, and that. Oh we come back with a bob or two. Yes, in three pound. Yes, and it was Blackpool. Mind you they've altered it a lot since then, oh what, they have, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Going errands for people. For me mother. When we wasn't going - with us - when it wasn't our turn to go into town.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 You told me about the shopping last time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 And Sundays was mostly three times church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh - oh yes. That was kept as a Sunday with everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you have different clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes. Always Sunday clothes and weekday clothes. Now today - they put 'em on any time, they don't do that work. Now we had a
 - a dress, coat and hat for Sunday. And you got your hat - and coat - and your - your weekday things for schooling and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Were you allowed to play games on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did your parents think it was wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well - you see, the - the - it were took up with - going to - Sunday schooland -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 So there wasn't much time left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 There wasn't much time left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Was there anything you couldn't do on Sunday, you wouldn't have been allowed to do that you might have wanted to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Couldn't spend money on a Sunday. You couldn't find a shop. And if you did you daren't - you daren't spend no money. You daren't go and buy anything, 'cos they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Would your parents have had a Sunday paper for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes, they always had Sunday papers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 So that was all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did your parents attend a place of worship?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, not with me mother - you know, having us to - look after and that. She used to feel -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 It was just the children who would go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes. She used to feel that she could do with the rest after she'd - you know, got the meals ready and washed all up and done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Your father didn't go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, he never - used to like to sit and smoke his pipe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 And you went twice a day and Sunday school didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes. Twice to Sunday school. And church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What denomination was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh it were Church of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Daybrook church did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes. Daybrook church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 And you went to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Yes. Used to go to Gedling. Southwell. In brakes, Mr Clowers used to have a place on here, he used to take us. Then you could go for the day and have your tea for one and three. And it were love
ly. We thought it was great. And a Band of Hope, we used to go to a Band of Hope and I used to sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What other social activities organised by the church did you take part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Dancing class, Bible Class. And - confirmation, confirmed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, not the choir, it was all - boys and men, Daybrook church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did the church run any temperance club?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, I can't remember 'em - not running temperance clubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you belong to any other club organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Only the Band of Hope. And that was teach you not to drink. And talk to you about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 You told me that you said grace when you finished a meal, did you say it before you began?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh for what we are about to receive may the Lord make us truly thankful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you say it, the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 I used to have to say it with being the eldest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes. Kneel down at side of your bed and say - say your - prayer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Well me mother used to stand there while we did it. And - if you said - if anything wrong she'd correct you. She used to say, now that - that's not right. Now - you've not been taught that and I've always it again, and then you can get into bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Can you remember how old you were when you started to do this? Or can you never remember not doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well I should say - I started - I didn't tell you this before - I was sent - I was - sent to school at three years of age 'cos they to
ok 'em then, three years of age. I was. I was sent to what they call - the Martinhall school, or was it Martin school, a boarding school, my mother paid four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14112074\charrsid12715645  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 pence a week for me for a long time. Four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14112074\charrsid12715645  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
pence a week she paid. That was at the - I don't know whether it was the National or the board school. I moved from one to the other when they took the four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14112074\charrsid12715645  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 pence off you see, that was dropped. But I kno}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14112074\charrsid12715645 w of others as had}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
 had that to pay, but mother told me she - had it to pay for me - and that. And - it was a school in Bulwell you know as I used to go to. Then you could pass from one to another. And - of course - now they'll not take 'em at that age. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 You can't remember being three and going to school can you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, not very well. I can't. I think
 I can just remember - yes. Yes, I think I can just remember - a little bit of it. Wearing a little pinafore, you know, round here and the - the fancy lace front. And - mother used to take me 'cos it was a nice way to - to go. And - think after a time - w
e
 went to - now I don't know whether it was the - boarding school we went to, or we come to the National or the National and we come to the boarding school. See, they changed us like, when you got so old. Well then that money came off. That all dropped alt
ogether. Then it was like what they call - a National school that was it. You didn't pay anything. You didn't have to pay anything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well he was a Conservative man, and he was very interested in that.
 So was my husband. He was a big man, me husband was, at - helping with that work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 So your father was Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Why do you think he held those views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well I don't know, he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 He didn't discuss it with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. But he was always - a dead Conservative, so was my husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 She was the same like, she'd - she - was on the Conservative side same my mother was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Was she sort of interested or do you think she was just going along with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 She were just along me mother wasn't - you know, not same as the men is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you remember your mother or father voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 And they would have voted Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes. Oh ye
s, there was - when Disraeli was - Prime Minister and - oh a - a lot of more of 'em as I can - you know, go through if I think like about them all but - different Prime Ministers as I can remember.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 In some places at that time men felt they risked los
ing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers. Do you know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well the brewery's a Conservative firm. No, I think he'd always been one. Yes. Always been - that, never voted no other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Was your father actually a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you remember him working for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. He didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 And your mother wouldn't have had time I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
No, she hadn't, she'd - you know, she'd enough - she used to have enough to do she said to look after the children and do us the - you know, do her duty to 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did your parents take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well mother always used to be sewing. Or - sometimes she'd sit and rest a bit and then - she'd - her machine and - start to make somethi
ng for us. Pull something to pieces you know how you do. Yes, and make a - a dress or a - pinafore or - underskirt or anything for - for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, I can't remember. Think she was a more at home bird.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, only just a walk out. And - we might have a walk on a Sunday night round to the Garden and that. That's about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Who would she go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 She would go with me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 When did your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 About six o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh he used to have several - like, you know, like night - several nights at the garden 'cos there was a lot to do. And - he'd p
erhaps - would have a - a night or two - resting you know, and that. Then he'd go and fetch - garden stuff, and if he didn't get - if he didn't go on Saturday fetch it he'd go early Sunday morning and fetch his vegetables and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did he attend any pubs or clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Only the Balfour. Same as my husband went to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Regularly did he go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did your mother ever go too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. Never. I never known my mother to ever go in a public house or anything. Or take a drink. Never. No, she wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, I don't think he did. I can't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did he attend the races ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, no race man. Oh no, he were quite again that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 So he wouldn't have approved of betting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. He'd listen to people but he wouldn't have anything to do with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, I think they only just had the - the - ordinary club as me dad used to pay, what they call a sick club. Yes, that's all, he
 used to go every - every Saturday night and it was held at the old Spot. In the top room. Of course, the Old Spot's different now to what then, used to go - a lot of stairs, facing the door as you went in, it was old then, and then you used to have to go
 into the - big room, take it there, clubmen used to sit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Boot or clothing clubs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Funeral expenses clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Insurances. Yes. They paid them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well all right but - me broth
er was - very - very nasty. And - of course when I - went with my husband - and that, then the war broke out - of course I was at home then, I wasn't married. I was at home, and my brother was at home, he wasn't married 'til - after. He always used to be 
o
n about - you know - on - on to me and I used to say well - it's all right, I said, but - I should like to know what I've done. And then he of course he were a - bit hasty. He used to say things and - then mother used to say, now you can stop it. We don't
 
want this. And he used to say - he used - he's turned round and he's said to me - time you went somewhere else to live. Mother said, you can stop that, we're not having that work here. We're not having it. So she said, you can stop it. I had a bit of that
 to put up with. But nothing much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What about the sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well, they was all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Was there one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 The one that died. She were very quiet but very nice. She was very good to my son when he was born, and 
that's going back to fifty-one years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well I'm sorry to say most on 'em's gone. Well I used to play with Edith Terry. The -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 The neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes, Lou Froggett. Francy Parr. Francy is living. Edith Terry's dead. Lou Froggett's been dead some years. And - S}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14112074\charrsid12715645 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 rah Turner. Of course her mother was midwife to me when I had - Lesley. And - we all used to go out together. And to Sunday school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 So you played more with friends than with the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Well we used to play - at the bottom of - just past the Daybrook church, where the - church house is built. Just - just a little past where the salt place is there. It used to be an old house. And - we used to play wit
h their daughter Waley, and he used to drive the engine to crush stones down on the road. And he used to keep it in his yard, it was - really a big - place, poultry and things, and we used to go in there and play - a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 This was in the garden there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
In their garden. And then we used to play - perhaps bottom of the street a bit. Or - look in the shop windows, the two - there was two shops then at - at bottom of Morris Street on Ridesfield Road, used to go and have a look there and then we perhap
s might have a little walk and then - come and play again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 We were talking about people being in different groups.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you remember the rough people and the un}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14112074\charrsid12715645 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 You said about a special section of cottages? Was it Dirty Row or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Dirt Yard, that was in the Daybrook bri}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14112074\charrsid12715645 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 ge, where the - garages is now, on the left}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14112074\charrsid12715645  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
hand side as you go down. Them was all houses at the back, very little small houses, some of 'em wasn't very clean you know, and a row on the front.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What sort of people lived in them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Well - with families. And - and that. They might have - they've been - one or two decent people and then there was the others as - wasn't quite so - you know, how - how people - lets the things go and lets themselves go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 In that time before 1918 did you think of some people as belonging to one and some sort o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14112074\charrsid12715645 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645  another group of people? You mentioned there were the middle and the first class and the third class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you think in those terms then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Well it was really a matter of this with some of them. If they - they'd had - held a - got a position - in them days as they thought it was - really something, they was it. But your parents - worked and they got a job. And - I couldn't see 
- I studied that up many a time, which I've done lately, recently. And - I used to think, well why? My - my - father works. My mother works at home and keeps us - clean, comfortable. Now then what difference - are they to me? See? But that was that. Just 
that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What sort of people belonged to the same group as yourself, you say people you thought of as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well they - the people as I'm - I - I knew like, as - we played with and went - went out with. And - and at school. Mind you, there w
ere some of these - men the fathers that - just got a little bit higher position, in them days, they - their children went to the same school as us. Well we're in same class, well we all used to be - friendly and that, but it was just the parents. See?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What sort of people belonged to the other groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well as - no, they wouldn't be - like our - because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 You mentioned dirty and ragged people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes, that's it and - and in them days you know - there was a lot - with dirty heads. In them d
ays there were a lot, and went to school and had to be sent home. Well - my mother always used to say - don't hang your clothes against them and don't put your heads against them or go with 'em. Because she were always at our hairs. See? Looking after tha
t
. Well today - there's none of that. There - there's been - stuff for it and it's - there's none on it. Well in them days the were a lot of that sort of work. Yes. And that was some of them that - wasn't too - great you know, clean, and that, of course - 
in them days there was all diff - all sorts went - together and all classes you know and that. But - they used to send them home from school if they seen anything or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Well - no, as - we was - taught - not to cheek your elders. And to mind your own business, and go about - and mind your own business. And if anyone said anything to you take no notice. That's what they used to say to us. An
d if they don't speak - don't you worry, go along. Mm. Minding your business. And that's what they used to say to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 And you told me you were told to curtsey to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What sort of people would you have curtsied to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well - 
anybody in a - a very good position. As came to the church and that. See, or a - Sunday school you know that came - came in. And that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did the boys in the family touch their caps to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes, oh yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Was there any other way in which the showed respect to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Well by bowing. Yes. I think that was about - you know, all. Or you was - taught anybody - anybody that was - certainly - somebody. For - you was taught to know what - who to say sir to and who not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Who would have been a sir when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Some had a title, some hadn't. Yes sir. No sir. We was taught that. Always taught that at school as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you have to say master or madam to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes, master. And - miss. You know, people that
 - took us - our teachers at Sunday school and that. And same at - weekday school, miss. And - if they was married, it was always M there was two there that were married, Mrs Bagley, Mrs Morris. Was taught - we was always told to address them like that. Y
es.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in those ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Oh yes. Yes, the vicar used to come, and the curate with him. And - then there used to be Miss Lees as I've told you down - at that lot - centre down there, when the Lees w
as there, they was very big - people. She used to come and visit you and see - if you was all right or - you know, and that, been in Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Would anyone have curtsied to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. No. No, there was none of that - in them days for 
- you know, like that. But - always - treat 'em with respect and manners. And always used to address - you know, always used to say Mrs Kerr. Always address 'em, and Mr Kerr. Always address 'em well like that. Never nothing else. And that. They just - how
 they - title if they was entitled to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 You told me some of the most important people round here, and you mentioned the Sealey's, I can't remember who else you mentioned now.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 The Lees, Bernard Lee and - and - Actons, they used to live at Goodwood
 House. On Redhill where they built all those houses now, that big ground, that - knocked that big house down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Who lived there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 The Atkins. Acton. Jimmy Acton. And his father, and they kept the White H.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 That's why there's an Acton Road is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Yes. Yes. And they kept the White Hart then. They did. In them days, well then - when - old - old Mr Acton died, and the son Jim - it was - turned over to the Farrs 'cos they were relations. Yes, they was like relations that come in. Robinson
s Farm and Actons. They was all big people. Sir John Robinson. He lived on Church Drive, Sir John lived at - Worksop. And - that's why they owned the houses was built in remembrance of his son as got killed. Thatos on yes, John Sansford. I can remember wh
en that funeral and they fired over his grave. Remember them days. Yes, well that's why - the alms houses were built in memory of him. Sir John - Sanford. And that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 You can in contact with these people through the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 That's it, all at - that's all church people. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Why were they considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Well I think it was merely because they - done a lot - for the church and - you know, and Potters, they - she was the organist, Mrs Potter was. Big fine woman. And Colonel Potter.
 That was his son and his father. They lived where the - Bedale Road where that hotel is now. What's the name? Riddiesdale Road. Well - theirs was a big house stood there and big grounds to it. Beautiful green grounds and lawns. And we used to go down the
re for - for - the - parties there for - you know, in the summer when they had these - I can't tell you now - garden parties. Yes, we used to go every year. And that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What about the shopkeepers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 I think everybody. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 It was a friendly sort of place was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Mm. Yes, it was in them days. Different to what it is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 They didn't keep themselves to themselves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. They always spoke to you and - when you went in they were very obliging.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What about the clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh Mr Vaughan used to come round, you young rascals he says, where have you been? He was a nice old - gentleman and his wife. They was.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 And teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Miss Dables. Miss Malcron. Miss Bull. They all had - they was all in good positions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did they associate with everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes. All three of them did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 I don't suppose there were many farmers down here were there? What about employers, did they keep themselves to themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Mr - there was - Farrs Farm up there, they'd got daughters and sons, they used to come to church. And - and that, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What sort of people would you say went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Respectable people. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What sort of people went to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well there was respectable people in them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Were they sort of different, could you describe any difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
No, I don't think so, only just a matter of - they was chapel and we was church. Think that's all the difference it was. Don't think it - them to their - religious place
s, ways, ours to ours you see. Church and chapel, it did - no, no, not to us. Mm. Well - the church - the people of the church people here you know they kept to it. And people as went to the Daybrook chapel and the other chapels up Front Street, you see, 
they all had their own - places to go to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 There are so many chapels here aren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh there is, my word. You're right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 When you were younger did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there 
were different groups?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well - there was some as lived - perhaps different to others. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Can you sort of describe a typical family in each groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well I - don't think there was much - much different really - and that. They all seemed to
 - be friendly and - help one another. As far as I knew like in my young days, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 You did say that you felt some families were thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes, well - of course that goes today the same don't it? That's 
the same thing today in - different - parts of the - Annold and Bestwood and - Daybrook. Then is the same people, sorts of people like that now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well - some on 'em - had
 had their training for joiners, plumbers and all that. Well - of course they worked for the firms you know, different firms which their fathers worked - there, well they all used to be - friendly and speak - all like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 And the wives would have been friendly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes. Difference, no. No, not in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people whether they were in different groups or classes or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, I don't think they was people in that type. Not in that class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 This must have been a much more friendly place than some, from what you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes - what - what it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social group or class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, she didn't. She didn't - mind yo
u she was a church - person before she was married and that but then they'd families and - and things to do, you see it really - occupied her time. But having four of us to look after and that. But she was a good living woman. Me mother was. Oh yes. And s
o was me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Was it possible at that time to move from one sort of class to another?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
No I don't think so, I think you just grow up and - you know - have - you would do, you were brought up and - you stay, and then - as you got older - you le
arn. You understood more. And then - it brought you then to go in - into - company, and go to concerts - to - to the chapels we used to go. There was no objection in that because - we all used to go to the concerts - then, orchestral concerts, you see in 
t
hem days - there was the brass band in Arnold too, two brass bands I think that were it. And - - then there was orchestral, big orchestral, well they used to have these here - orchestral concerts - in the schoolrooms at the chapel and - their churches, we
ll we used to pay }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14112074\charrsid12715645 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645  three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14112074\charrsid12715645  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 pence and sixpence in them days, and they used to be lovely concerts. Pass hours - you know, do - a - hour or two on, like that. And - we used to - go to them when - there was these concerts. And that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Got to think back a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 It doesn't sort of strike you immediately, that somebody was described that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well I think it was only in the Sealey's line. And of course they - had got it. Se
eley's was very big people you know. They all - old Mr Seeley and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 He might have been described as a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Why would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 I think he was a very nice - you know, and that, and - them that worked for him - th
ey always said he was a nice person. But he was a - man like this. Them as told me that worked for him - that - he would never have a egg - that had got a light yolk. Wouldn't have it. Always liked a deep - because he - he'd no - never - liked 'em at all,
 it wasn't right. Well them told me as worked for him. And - that. See, the butlers and them you know, and that, and it - somebody told me - as the butler told. And they told me. About that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What happened if he got a light one by mistake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 He woul
dn't have it. Wouldn't accept it. Oh they daren't take it on the table. No. No, there was a - you know - kept - a lot of servants and - things up there you know, up there at Bestwood Lodge there, where it is up the - you know, on the - on the Man}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14112074\charrsid12715645 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 field Road. Which it was then them days Rampon, now it's Mansfield Road. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes, Mr Boot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well he was a nice fine man. Very stern. And he'd soon
 box your ears with his gloves if he thought you were doing anything you ought not to do. Yes, he did. Mr Boot. He lived in - the second house from the shop at top of street. And - they both died there, Mrs Boot and Mr. They were both well - built people.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 When you were naughty did your mother ever say I'll call the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 She - used to tell us she'd send for the policeman. If we did it - again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 How do you think he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes, he were very stern on the police force t
hen, and - and then there was the Inspector Bishop. He was another one. Then there was Bobby Hornsey, he was another. And Wilson. As I remember in Arnold.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 When you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 How do you think they treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well - wouldn't let 'em get away you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Were they fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Well they were fair. But they were strict. They were strict in them days. But Mr Boot lived on street. I know - his - his - I've heard me - my husband say - many a time if they've - have stood tal
king together, he's come and he's said - now then, and he's biffed them with a glove - with his gloves, come on, break up. He wouldn't have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 When you were young was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes. Mr - Mr Cope was - our landlord when we lived up - up - Morris Street when we first came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 He was a very nice man. But - and he'd got a lovely wife, she was very nice when she came for the rent. But 
he was a man - he liked beer. That were the only thing - but he was a real gentleman, and Mrs was real nice too, and that, they were very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh very often. On their little wage you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well I used to think, well - some day we shall be able to help them. Be glad when we've left school and come to - we go}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14112074\charrsid12715645  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 to work. That's how we used - we used to think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
They'd only got the club money. He paid in a sick club. And that's all he got, what they called - now what was it - Royal - Royal - the Buffaloes or something. I just forget now, and we u
sed to have to go to the Old Spot and - take it every Saturday night. You just go straight up and up some stairs. And - and straight down and back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 How often was this that he was out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well it was when - illness that he - as he had 
to draw on the club. But if he was out of work - there were no - unemployment money then. Nothing. The only thing that could do was apply to the parish, and you'd got to chance then whether you got it or not. And it won't be a deal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did your family ever get help from the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Can you remember anyone who did and how they were treated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Well some got it. But it wouldn't be a very big amount. It'd only be about three and six they'd grant 'em. And then they'd want to know - all y
our business, all the full details of everything, right into it. Now Mr Ellis was the man for that. He lived in the Bays, up Front Street, where the police station is now, just past there there used to be a row of bays, and he lived there. Old Mr Ellis di
d. But he was very strict - if you got anything - I've heard 'em say you were lucky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Was there someone in the district who the people disapprove of very strongly, was there any special way in which they showed it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well I think by not having anything to do with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you remember anyone being made to leave by rough music? Do you know what I means?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Mean - made to - to go in a hurry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 It means sort of clattering and banging and making a noise outside their houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 To show that you disapprove of what they've done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Disapprove of it. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you know anything about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes, there was in our time. And if they were - if they made a - it made a lot noise, you could have it stopped - by reporting 
to the police. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 In some parts of the country apparently suppose a woman had misbehaved with someone else, they'd go and make a banging outside her house.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes, they would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 As a sort of form of disgrace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Grace, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did it ever happen here, have you ever heard of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
No, I can't remember any. I can't remember - only when - men had had - some men had had too much. Well then there'd be a little bit - noisy, but - they were making noise, but the - went - I think they went home quietly with singing and doing you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 This is the good people making a noise to annoy the naughty people in theory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Mm. Yes. The other, that's it. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Have you ever heard about effigies being made? Sort of witchcraft business, when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Well - now there did used to be - say there was like - that thing, and they used to say - you could go to certain people - and they'd burn this dragon's blood, on the fire.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well that was - to kill
 a spirit, or kill a - enemy. That was done. That was in our time. That used to go on, and it used to be talked on a lot. And was done. But I never went - never knowed 'em on it, only heard of it. And talked of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you know what the dragon's blood was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well I really don't know. It used to be a dragon's blood. It used to say, it used to put a curse on people. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Have you heard of anything else like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, only fortune telling and - all like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Were they taken seriously?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Fortune tellers, they used to - sort of read your cards or your hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did people believe it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Oh a lot of people did. And I don't doubt that while there wasn't them - that did it - some of 'em - give 'em the truth. Yes. I once remember going to one with some - some girls from work. You know I - you know I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Was it at a fair or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
No. On Saturday, and you know how you are when you work together, they tell you these things, they say, oh you ought to go, come on and go with us
. They - we used to think it more for fun. Well then - I went - with 'em, and in Exchange Walk - Can York, big fine person, nice person, she had a palmist place there up some steps. And - I remember going there, with two of 'em from work and when got ther
e
 I said, I - I can't - I'm not going in, I'm a bit frightened. Says, come on, it's - easy, and - nowt to be - frightened of. But anyway I went in, but I know I remember - I didn't much like it. And they went in and had their told - and then I had to go in
,
 paid a shilling. And - she says, I remember he saying - are you frightened? I said, no. She said, I think you are but - my dear girl, don't you be frightened of me. So I says - she says, I shall never hurt you. But she told me some truth about - my husba
nd and I didn't know then about - him. Mm. Described how he walked and everything. And that was the one. That's the only time as ever I ever - had anything to do with - you know anything like that. Parents didn't believe in it. And I never told 'em.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Can you remember any sort of old wives tales you learnt when you were young that you discovered were not true?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh I don't know. There was a lot of things - they used to say in them days. But I just can't get 'em. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Like gooseberry bushes and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
That's it. Oh they used to say - the stork's brought baby, or they got them from under a gooseberry bush. We was told that 'til we were - ever so and thought it were right you know 'til we got older. And that. And if you was - anywher
e - and anybody was - shouting or anything and you just - turned to look or - or anything, they used to say - it's all right, we don't want no one to hold the letter box, pig ain't going to be shaved. That's what they used to say to you. Yes. I often thin
k
 about that when that woman starts. Mm. Aye. But I can't think of - no, there's such a lot of things in them days different, which has all gone now dead. There's all different - words and meanings for them - now. Used to - and the boys and - and girls use
d to play at - at - knocking on doors, larking. And we used to tie door handles together. Then when they'd done all that they used to run away - and people - couldn't get out 'cos they'd tied 'em together. Boys used to do a lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Could they do that on any night of the year or was it just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, they'd do it any - dark nights, if they were out playing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 In Yorkshire they used to do this on the night before November the fifth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, well - mm. Mm. Yes. And - then there was what they ca
lled - they used to - certain date in January, it were what they called - when farmers used to hire - the men to work for them, and - used to call it - what day was it? Ploughboy licking night. And they used to - farmers used to - you know, hire the farm 
l
abourers and you could - they could go from - one farm to another, and - and that, if they wished to, or if not they could stop. Well that night - they used to - black their faces, the children did, the boys, and go round - you know and that. Ploughboy li
cking night as they called it. That was a night when - the - the - farmers hired the - the - farm labourers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 And the boys blacked their faces?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Faces and do yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What else did they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 They used to go round - singing and doing. Mm. Sort
 of a - game at night, they enjoyed it - and that. None of that now. All that - Mrs King told me they were never allowed to use nicknames in their family, and were told not to answer if they were called by nicknames.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Can you tell me what games you played when you were a schoolgirl, can you remember any special ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Marbles. Hopscotch. And - hide and seek. And - oh in - one shutting their eyas - and counting to three while you - hid yourself and they come to find you. And - what else did we play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you play anything like kick-out can?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, no. No I don't think we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 One kicked the can and the others ran away and hid while it was being redeemed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh we have played that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What did you call it, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh I don't know now, I can remember playing that. Different names you see. Yes that's it. No, I don't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well we did get dirty but - parents used to say where have you been - to get in a mess like that, 
you didn't go out like it. But still - it were off - off with them clothes and - some more on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 They were fairly understanding about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes, as long as they were respectable 
and all right. But if there was - children as made us stray - led you astray, or - used to say - dirty words, they'd make you keep away from them. They wouldn't have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Can you think of any other reason why you might have been kept away from other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
When they was cheeky. Yes, when they was very cheeky, the - the - used to make you understand you'd not got to go with them. You keep away. And if you don't well you know what you're going to have when you - you come back again.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, only the Band of Hope. And that was like a temperance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 At what age could you belong to this band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh I should be in me - me young age about - ten or twelve, somewhere there. Yes. Oh yes, we h
ad that, but - there were only like - dancing at the institute - church institute and - and then you know parties and - just that. There wasn't - every such a lot in them days. No, we used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 I should like to ask you how you spent your free time when you were at school, did you have any hobbies then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Oh we used to knit. We used to knit and - and do. But - of course I think I'm told you before, we had - so much - seaming to do, and - drawing, drawing lace work, the threads out. That, we used to have to do that. Help to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you keep any pets at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Always a cat. Always a cat. Me dad was very fond of a cat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you collect anything as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, I don't think I did, I can't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did the girls do any gardening or was it just the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Just me father - me - me - father did all that. Mind you we used to have to go at - at - when it was potatoes - to set, and he used to show us how to - set them, the distance apart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 So you did help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes. We used to have to 
go to garden and - and help with them. Have 'em you know - so that the - not knock the sports off 'cos you were - you - you got into trouble if you did, put the sports up - you see, so much apart, we used to have to - he learnt us how to do that. Then he 
filled in. See? Used to have to and do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
I - I'd take a jar up, get little minnows. Oh yes, we used to go down agen - where that - where that - that - Factories Lane is now, wasn't like that. It was Factories Lane to botto
m and then a little dyke run, and we used to go down there under the little bridge, and that. And then down Jacob's Ladder, that was Bury Road. Oh well, used to be - where the water and there's some runs now you know, in - on the Valley Fields. We used to
 go down there, down Jacob's Ladder and - go there. Get our feet wet through and then - of course there we was. Aye, we used to go and fish, the fishing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you go for walks a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes, we used to go all round. Pond Hill. And - up to what th
ey call the Rookery, that were where the police station was. And - they used to be gardens then. And we used to go all round there, and all up Barkers Fells, all up Fre}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14112074\charrsid12715645 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645  Hill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you go bicycling? It wasn't your bike I take it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. No, I never went no more after that. It sort of - you know, sort of frightened me a bit. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Who did you do these things with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 A friend of mine. Which of course is dead and buried now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 The same sort of age as you was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes. She's passed away now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Only the school sports, that was all. Running and that. That's all, there wasn't so - too much in them days you know. There was a little but not - about you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you go to any theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh y
es. Went to the Royal. And when there was the Empire and the Hippodrome then, used to go to them, there was very good shows. And I went a lot to the theatre, both me and Mr King did, and - and before. But not -
