I only run - what was it - a pound. A pound and - about twenty-two shilling I think, twenty-two or twenty - somewhere there, I can't exactly think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you remember how much you gave to your mother in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Well - I used - I used to pay me board when I was at home. And then when we came to live with - with Mr King's mother, I think I paid her - how much was it? About thirty-five - shillings, somewhere there because thin
gs was cheaper, and you didn't pay the board as you had to - as you pay now. See. I think it was - about you know, somewhere about - thirty-four shilling, I'm not exactly sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 So we can't ask if your husband helped with jobs in the house and things like that, because he wasn't there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
He wasn't there, no. My word, when you look back Mrs - Jacob - and think - you you've turned eighty, and you think of your - marriage - marriage - you know - been married forty-nine years, we was only a month or tw
o off of the fiftieth anniversary. Yes. And now I look back and think - how things has altered, how things has changed, how things have improved, and so different, you can never believe it. Memories. I try to - think back a lot more. Names I've tired to b
ring back and - yet they don't come, they don't come to me just - you know - can't get them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 When you were living with your mother when you first married how many rooms were in the house there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Three bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Were there any relatives or lodgers living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. No one, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Any paid help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes, all washing and everything done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 And your husband wasn't there for jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. No, he was a - abroad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What sort of room was used for bathing in in Portland Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Well you mostly had a - had - the - kitchen where the fire was - at - either what they was out - in a day time when they knew they was going and they used to tell you you know and you could - fetch the bath up, yes. Yes. Or at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you make clothes yourself then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, mother did. She did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Even when you were that age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Where were meals eaten at that house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 In the kitchen like this. All of the work wa
s done in the - kit - you know, the - what we call - well the - the name then was - the scullery. Now then it was the kit - it's the kitchen now. Now they give the names - them days it was - the dining room. The lounge. And all that, it got to that from -
 
where - it used to be the front room. The living room. The front room. Parlour. Then it got to front room from parlour, that's - what they used to be. Always the parlour. And now - and now it's the front room. Now it's got from all that - to the sitting r
oom, the lounge, the dining room. I can't do it in here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you ever have meals in any other room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
No - we - we've had - usually used to have - mother had a big table, for cutting out on and that, and - she always used to prepare in there and th
en set this table. And it were very rare we - had any - anything in front, unless it was a - a - like a sandwich or a biscuit or anything like that, later on at night. Then we might have - sit and have it in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 And the cooking was done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 In the - kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Where was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 So it was just as you told me in your younger days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 It really wasn't any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No different. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you do any cooking or did your mother do it all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well 
- as we got older - we had cookery lessons at the school. And we used to have to take a - exercise book, and we used to have to write down - what did - what they called the dictation. She used to - the teacher used to read it out to us, what we'd got to p
u
t in the cake, what had to be put in, and in soups and all that. Well - you used to have to write all this down in your exercise book. And then she'd look at it to see if you'd got it all correct. Well then after you done that, you used to have get - get 
y
our apron on, and your - things like, and go to the table, and get your bowl and weigh the flour out - the amount you want, and the - you know, the - not butter, marg we used to have and - but there did used to be butter put in 'cos it was cheaper then th
a
n it is now, they could afford to do it, and - she used to weigh it all out to us and that, put it in the bowl, and then we all used to have to stand in different places with the bowl round a - a very big table, and we used to have to - mix it together an
d
 do, and put it in the tin, grease the tin - tins, piece of paper round and - and she used to put it all in the big oven. Then she used to - give - so much time for cooking. Well you'd all that to - to go and write down, like a gallery you sat in. You'd a
ll had to - write down.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What did you do on Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Well we used to go - we used to go out - for walks or - or to see some friends, with - you know, your companion and that. Or we've gone to Trent Bridge, and Arborstum. See we've gone to them places, and passed the time on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days? During the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well we worked - we worked - on a Saturday, 'til twelve o'clock. And - they didn't pay 'til Saturdays some days, used to have to work 't
il twelve, and we used to come home, and - and - get - have a dinners, wash, change - and - then we used to go out. Well - before I was married - or the war broke out, when I were going with me husband, we used to go down to see Notts play, he was a very 
b
ig Notts man. Yes. And - of course you could take your young ladies. We used to go in the stand and I used to go with him. I got very excited you know. I used to turn on him. It got me a bit excited and I thought, oh dear this is getting me a bit excited.
 I - used to enjoy going. I used to know all about all the players and - everybody then. Well - every fortnight we used to go down to see Notts play and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 What did you do on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well - we had to help at home in the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2953006\charrsid12715645  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 morning. Washing pots up and - and then get washed and changed ready for dinner. Set the table and - and wash the dinner pots and - and do all that, and then we could - go out then like, so we used to go a walk - round.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you wear special clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes. They wasn
't like they are today. You used to have Sunday clothes and weekday clothes. You couldn't put them on regular unless you was going somewhere. And your hair all - your hair washed, used - and used to have it plaited and then - done out, it used to look bea
utiful. Of course I'd more hair then than I've got now. Lost a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Were Sunday clothes very different from weekday clothes, or did old Sunday clothes turn into weekday clothes afterwards?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes, used to turn them when they could like, down to 
the other - other, and make them for them, and that. But we always had different good Sunday clothes. And - weekday clothes. But they was different than your weekday clothes. Your weekday clothes was put away - 'til Monday morning again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you think it was wrong to work or enjoy yourself on a Sunday or didn't you think it mattered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well we didn't go and - we never enjoyed our - we never went - to any enjoyment on Sunday. Only to Sunday school, and then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 When you were older what did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 I never went to no - no - entertainment on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you feel it was really wrong or was it what you were used to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well in them days it was wrong. Biggest majority of people - my age or older would tell you that. The old p
eople - didn't believe in shops being open. Nothing like that. You couldn't buy anything on a Sunday. It was kept as a good day, and a holy day. Very good. In our time, but now - it's got past everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 When you first married did you attend a place of worship or not on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
I did before - before Mr King came home, and then he came - when he had finished and came home you see - with going on with - with Lesley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Up to the end of 1918 you would have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 This was the same church was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Mm. Daybrook church, yes. Daybrook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 How often did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well - sometimes - we used to go - to the service in the morning - in our turns different Sundays. And - Bible Class in the afternoon.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Even when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Yes, while I was at home. And Mr King was abroad - I went. And then - I used to go to church - a - a Sunday night and then come home again then. Unless - I went with me friends - to her house, which we often did, and we had supper the the mother 
- Mrs Turner, she was a midwife you know, and - mother and dad and them was always very friendly with living at Bulwell - with them and knowing \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 Well I used to go there - and she used to - walk back up the - cook the ta - tatoes you know, warm t
hem up, and the greens all together, and then cut the joint. And give you all of you would sit round and have your supper. Just a make love - a lovely supper for us like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 When your husband was on leave did he come to church with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Occasionally he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, it was a boy - boys choir. Boys choir, all boys in them days. No girls choir. All boys and - and the men you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 When you were first married did the church run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No
. None whatever. The only temperance - place we went to - was in me younger - younger days, we got older, was what they called the Band of Hope, and it was held at the Daybrook school, and - the Sunday school teachers - used to used to take us - in saying
 
- in saying poetry, recitations they used to say then, and singing. Well Miss Bull used to take us. She lived at bottom of the laundry yard. There used to be two houses where that - parking is now. From the Old Spot. Two big houses. Well Mr Bull - was the
 manager of the Daybrook laundry. And his daughter Emma was a Sunday school teacher, and she used to ta us in the Band of Hope - for practice, and we used to go to her house - to practice the singing, and - saying the - recitations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 This was during the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 That's - the - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 You'd stopped by then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Stop - I'd stopped then going. I - think -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 During the war did you belong to any other clubs organized by the church at all
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, the only thing I done during the war - was help the 
Daybrook Baptist chapel to knit scarves and - balaclavas, used to do a lot of them, and Mrs Horton in the Cottage Row was - same age as me, she went to school same time and that, she used to come and bring me the wool, and fetch me others back. And I used
 to do that during the war, to help - for the boys, and that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 When you were living at home during the war was grace said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well - we - they used to - used to stand up and say - for what we are about to receive may the Lord make us truly 
thankful. Then when we'd finished we used to say - thank the Lord for my good tea or dinner, and bless the Lord for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you take this in turns or do it as a group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh used to take it in turns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you have family prayers at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well - you know the - there - there was always - kneel at side of bed and say - Our Father, God in Heaven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 But not as a group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Not as I grew older. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 At this stage did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, I - rarely - you know - ca
n't say that I did, but - I used to listen to me - to me dad like. He - he was one that - would always go to the meetings. A very big Conservative man. So was my husband. So - I used to learn a bit off - of - me dad, and off my husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 So your husband was Conservative too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you really sort of think about it much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
No, I just used to - go along and - understand who was going to be - who was in Parliament and who was going to take the seat next and - all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did your husband take much interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well - he never \{BLANK\}
 because the same as he said, there's a lot to politics. You've got to be very careful - if you enter that. And know what you're doing. Always used to say that. And know what you're saying. It
's no good anybody going - and - into them things he used to say, not knowing - what they're doing, they must be well educated, and understand. Well a lot of things he under - he understood, that I didn't nad he told me, see, I - that's how I used to lear
n like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Do you know why he was a Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 I don't know, he always was. His parents was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you or your husband vote in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, he was abroad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, I couldn't. No. No, I never done any. Not 'til after I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did either you or your husband ever feel under any pressure from anyone to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 You didn't feel anybody minded who you voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, I don't think - they - never told one another who they voted for. It was just kept - private.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Were you a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you ever work for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, I won't say I did. This was - after I was married. I 
used to sell poppies - and that, and I used to sell the - old - for disabled and the Boulevard, we did a lot for them. And we used to sell the - flowers for them and we used to go in - we used to go and see them. That's all I - that's all I've ever had, i
n -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did your husband join a political party ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. Can't never remember him joining.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 When you were not doing your work how did you spend your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Being in the house. Well it was different you see - with the war being on. That was 1914. War. Wasn't it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 This is just between your marriage and the end of the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes. Well - when this war broke out - I had gone - to see a friend at Sherw
ood with a - with this - friend's sister. And when we got to top of Sherwood Hill - they started shouting, war broke out. Well - we were - we was really astonished. My husband - was away with the Territorials - at - Scarborough. Well they demobbe 'em from
 
there. And he had to go to Derby. Some says Darby, some says Darby. Anyway up, they demobbed 'em and they had to go to a - the schools at Derby. And oh dear, oh dear, my - my inside turned over, well I remember it quite well. Both of us was alike. And I t
h
ought, oh dear, war. And - we came home. And we said like to them - that - that - papers had been out, they said yes, they'd been up there shouting - Posts, war broke out. And they'd had to demob them quick because on 'em landing in France. Which they did
 
you know. And - anyway up - I had a letter - from - my young man then, and he said - they were demobbed - and they'd had to come away from - Scarborough quick - to - to there, and he couldn't get - home - would I - tell his mother to send him some clean s
h
irts and things, and would I - try and come up on the Friday and bring them - and his mother to come as well. Well we went up to these schools - and - his mother didn't go. Sergeant Bell's wife went with me. She was going and she said she'd go along with 
m
e. Well we went together. And - she was taking the - her husband's some - clean things. And when we got there he told us they was demobbed. And he didn't know where they were going from there. But they'd have to do a lot of marching, and they did. And - t
hat was - that was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2953006\charrsid12715645  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
that, well they moved from there I don't know exactly where they went. They went - further away somewhere, billeted. Now where did they go from - there? I'm thinking. Where they went to. I don't - I don't recall - just we - remind that. J
ust where they went. But anyway - he was always on the - they were always on the move. And you see they had drop - drafted a lot into France. Well my husband - had got what they call a varicose vein, in his leg. And they wouldn't pass him. Mor}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2953006\charrsid12715645 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645  particular 
then than what they are now you know. Don't matter now, they rush you in. And - anyway up - he was disappointed because they wouldn't pass him with this varicose vein. He wanted to go abroad. Well anyway up later on - he didn't say anything to me he was g
o
ing abroad. Never said a word. And then - I don't know whether - his mother or someone told - told me, and I said, well I didn't know they was going abroad. I said, I thought - they hadn't passed him. Oh they said, they passed him this time, he wants to g
o abroad and he's going abroad. And he went. He went - into France. And he was in France - you know - during the - war and that. Then and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 How did you spend your evenings after you were married and before he came home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well we used to go to conc
erts - and that. But - there was - blackouts you know. And one thing and another. And - it was terrible. Terrible. When the zeppelins came over. Oh dear oh dear. I shall never forget Valley Road and all round. For them zeppelins, firing and banging - from
 
Bestwood - and you used to have to - keep indoors and - and - and - and that, you daren't go out. So there was no chance - of going out much. And it were - it come worse in the second world war. Because they blacked us out altogether. You daren't show a l
i
ght. But - any road you were always - always on - the alert for the postman. To see if they were safe. To get a letter. And with working in the factory and the - other - people's husbands and young men were there, they used to say, have you had a letter? 
I
 haven't. I said yes I'd had one and - he was safe up to writing that. Well then - they - they'd perhaps get one to say - whether they were safe or not. See you was all the time on the - moving, and that. Oh it was a worrying time that was, during the fir
st world war. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 So you did go to concerts then sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you go to theatres ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes. Yes, we went to the pictures too. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Cinemas were going then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 In Nottingham, yes. At Goldsmith Street and there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Music halls were there in the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes, they were in that time. In the first world war. Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 At that stage did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Used to do a lot of reading, books. And I used to do a lot of crocheting. Knitting. Yes. Used to do -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you have any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. We only had a cat. Me dad was very fond of a cat, he'd always have a cat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 You didn't do gardening, it was your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 He did that, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did either you or your husband at that stage go to any clubs, institutes or pubs?
