\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well he'd be a sweeper up. Sweeper up. But that's what they used to say. Where's the shack}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16415534\charrsid12715645  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 lad gone? Well then it was what wed call a sweepe
r up. Used to sweep all the rooms up. Well then when the - they'd - been at that a bit, and they wanted a boy on one of the frames with the men, he used to go and learn to work the frame, and - and work with this man. Man used to have two frames. And then
 
- he learnt the boy. And the boy used to - work one frame and watch it while the other - you know, that's how it used to be. Always used to be in what they call - one alley. Was - big long frames you know then, in that - took a lot - oh took a lot of runn
ing. And that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Did you feel that there were divisions of interests among workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Well - they all seemed interested in - mm - in one another you know, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers, did you feel that or not?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 
Well there were because some of them belonged a union. Just a union then, what they call the - Stockingers Union. But it wasn't - so much - as it is now, with unions. And that. But - they all seeme
d as if they was - all right like what I - when I worked with them, I worked with a lot of men, with men all the time. Yes. There's only two winders, to - winders in that room first. Then when the new building was built - we went into the - new building, 
well there was about two, four, six of us then. See it was a big long room and all machines put in, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Would you say that full time work changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. During the - war - we put - we worked 'til eight o'clock
. That was what the call - overtime, and we had a bit of bonus. Well it just made your money a little bit more. Just a little bit. And that's - about all. Of the - you know - in - as regards money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 When you became a full time wage earner were you treated very differently at home. Did you suddenly get treated differently or anything?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No, they - they had your wages and gave you some spending money. You had to be
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 This was to sort of soften it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Yes. And - used to be onto bobbin. Well then
 they used to like - have so many bobbins round, and you used to put it into a - a big round - tin then for them, as they used to carry it in, they used to take it down, and put it on the machine, on the - frame. And that. Then at night they took it off, 
put a damp cloth on it and then it were damp for next morning to work again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 I hadn't realized you had to keep this damp.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Oh yes. I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7885863 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 Was it very hot and wet in Morley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16415534\charrsid12715645 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 s or not very?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6896403 AK  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11173682\charrsid12715645 No. Oh you got some wet from the - stuff as it w
ent round then at times, it used felt it come out. Then there was - thread, what they call brown thread, that made - some - different toes for different - stuff and that.
